All Classes

Class Description
Board
A model to manage a two-dimensional array of Pieces during setup and play.
Game
An model used to hold two Players and a Board, representing and managing all relevant data used in the game.
GameDriver
A singleton that contains the shared information used between the different JFrames that make up the user interface and provides a way to handle state changes throughout the game.
GameDriver.GameState
Provides a list of the possible states the game can be in.
GameInitPanel
Displays two panels to select a color and name to be associated with each player.
GamepieceColorChooser
Allows a player to select a color to use to paint the template piece image with.
GamePlayPanel
Displays the board and its pieces, allowing for a player to move its own pieces and attack opposing pieces.
GameSetupPanel
Displays the board and the unplaced pieces of the current player and allows the player to place these unplaced pieces in an arrangment of their choice on their side of the board.
GameView
GameView is the JFrame that displays when the player selects 'Start New Game' from the main menu and allows the players to begin setup of the game and play Stratego.
GraphicButton
Draws an image that responds to mouse input and notifies an array of listeners when the button is pressed.
GraphicPanel
Displays a JPanel with a background image.
MainMenuView
Displays the main menu of the game to the user.
OptionMenuView
OptionMenuView is the JFrame that displays when the player selects 'Options' from the main menu and allows the player to change options that affect gameplay from the main menu.
Piece
Piece classes contain information concerning a game piece's rank, unique ID, and owner Player.
Player
Contains a player's identifying information and information relevant to the number of remaining pieces of each type that a player can still place down.
Stratego
The Stratego class creates an instance of the GameDriver singleton and calls GameDriver.openView to open the game's user interface.
TextureManager
TextureManager is a singleton class which loads and stores the images, colors, and borders to be used in the game.
UserDisplayPanel
A JPanel used to display a Player's information on the left side of the GameView, corresponding to the player whose turn it is.
